dc_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Grajewo, sheet L-17. A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Grajewo, Poland. Polyconic projection. Russian belt 4 grid. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Compiled from Germany, 1:25,000, German General Staff, 1925; Poland, 1:100,000, Military Geographic Institute, sheets 34-35, 1929; 34-36, 1930; 35-35, 1930 and 35-36, 1930. Road classification in Poland based on British intelligence reports, 1943.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
